## Getting Started

### Prerequisites

- [Salesforce CLI](https://developer.salesforce.com/tools/salesforcecli) with plugins:
  ```bash
  sf plugins install lightning-flow-scanner
  sf plugins install sfdx-git-delta
  sf plugins install sfdmu
  ```
- [Node.js](https://nodejs.org/) (LTS)
- [Claude Code](https://claude.ai/claude-code) with plugins:
  ```bash
  claude plugin add superpowers
  claude plugin add commit-commands
  claude plugin add code-review
  claude plugin add {sf-toolkit-repo-url}
  ```

### Setup

1. Clone this repository
2. Run `npm install` (installs Husky git hooks)
3. Authenticate to your Salesforce orgs:
   ```bash
   sf org login web --alias {dev-sandbox} --instance-url https://test.salesforce.com
   sf org login web --alias {production} --instance-url https://login.salesforce.com
   ```
4. Set default orgs:
   ```bash
   sf config set target-org {dev-sandbox}
   sf config set target-dev-hub {production}
   ```
5. Open in Claude Code and run `/setup`

